            <title>[SWTES0707-66] [TG-5] [Teodora] No error message when full name has too many characters</title>
                <link>http://jira.softacad.bg/browse/SWTES0707-66</link>
                <project id="11900" key="SWTES0707">SW_Test_07_07_2020	</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The problem is related to a field in the signup function.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Steps to reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Navigate to website:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;http://poll-app7-20200409.softacad.bg/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://poll-app7-20200409.softacad.bg/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Click Signup&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Type full name that is 41 characters long in the Full Name field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Expected result: A warning should appear that the full name should be a maximum of 40 characters and the border of the field box should become red.&lt;br/&gt;
Actual result: no error message appears/the border of the field box stays black.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
